General Com Pany Code of Conduct

1. Introduction

The following code of conduct (the "Code") sets out the standards of behavior that all employees of General Com Pany ("General Com", "we", "us", or "our") are expected to uphold. This Code is based on our company values of professionalism and dedication to our work.

2. Core Values

All employees of General Com are expected to uphold our core values of professionalism and dedication to our work. These values include, but are not limited to:

- behaving in a professional manner at all times;
- completing all duties and tasks assigned in a timely and efficient manner;
- respecting the confidentiality of company information; and
- using company resources only for company business.

3. Organizational Code of Conduct

All employees of General Com are expected to adhere to our organizational code of conduct. This code of conduct includes, but is not limited to:

- behaving in a way that does not bring discredit to General Com;
- complying with all applicable laws and regulations;
- adhering to our company policies and procedures; and
- reporting any potential violations of this Code.

4. General Employee Conduct

All employees of General Com are expected to adhere to our general employee conduct policy. This policy includes, but is not limited to:

- treating all fellow employees, customers, and vendors with respect and courtesy;
- refraining from any form of harassment or discrimination;
- using company resources only for company business;
- being honest and transparent in all communications; and
- refraining from engaging in any activity that could be considered a conflict of interest.

5. Social Media

All employees of General Com are expected to adhere to our social media policy. This policy includes, but is not limited to:

- not using social media to post confidential or proprietary information about General Com;
- not using social media to make negative or disparaging comments about General Com, our employees, customers, or vendors;
- using social media in a way that is respectful and professional; and
- refraining from using social media while on company time, unless it is for company business.

6. Conflicts of Interest

All employees of General Com are expected to adhere to our conflicts of interest policy. This policy includes, but is not limited to:

- disclosing any potential conflicts of interest to a supervisor or manager;
- recusing oneself from any situation in which there is a potential conflict of interest;
- refraining from using company resources for personal gain; and
- adhering to all applicable laws and regulations regarding conflicts of interest.

7. Outside Activities

All employees of General Com are expected to adhere to our outside activities policy. This policy includes, but is not limited to:

- refraining from engaging in any activity that could be considered a conflict of interest;
- disclosing any outside activities that could be considered a conflict of interest;
- obtaining prior approval from a supervisor or manager before engaging in any outside activity; and
- adhering to all applicable laws and regulations regarding outside activities.

8. Enforcement

Employees who violate this Code may be subject to disciplinary action, up to and including termination of employment.
